i)Name different types of operators in JS.

*Arithmetic Operators

*Comparison (Relational) Operators

*Logical Operators

*Assignment Operators

*Unary Operators

*Ternary (Conditional) Operator

*String Operators (optional for interview)

*Bitwise Operators (rarely asked)



i)Arithmetic: “Math operations (+, -, *, /).”

ii)Comparison: “Compare two values (==, ===, >).”

iii)Logical: “Combine conditions (&&, ||, !).”

iv)Assignment: “Assign or update values (=, +=).”

v)Unary: “Single value operators (++ , --, typeof).”

vi)Ternary: “Short if-else (condition ? value1 : value2).”

vii)Give example of arithmetic, logical, comparison, assignment, unary, ternary operators.





15. ES6 Operators (Spread & Rest)

i)Difference between spread and rest operators.

*Spread → Expands values

*Rest → Collects values


ii)Give example of spread operator with array.

*Used to expand array elements.
Tamil: Array-oda values-a velila spread pannum.
Example:
let arr1 = [1, 2, 3];
let arr2 = [...arr1, 4, 5];

console.log(arr2); // [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]

iii)Give example of rest operator with function parameters.

*Used to collect multiple arguments into an array.
Tamil: Function-ku varra extra values ellam orae array-la collect pannum.
Example:
function add(...numbers) {
  return numbers.reduce((sum, num) => sum + num, 0);
}

console.log(add(10, 20, 30)); // 60
